CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 12, 1963, pg. 8 reads: "Monster Masks - Art Barnes and Elizabeth Diggs won prized for wearing the ugliest masks at the Green Link Golf Club's affair at the Green Oaks Country Club dur [during] the recent holiday. Miss Diggs wore a badge which read: "I Hate Sex."  With her mask, one could see why. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Art Barnes and Elizabeth Diggs wearing masks, posed on bench in Green Oaks Country Club during the Green Link Golf Club's Masked Ball
